	      				<p>Cultural stereotypes around food remain, according to Marilyn Morgan, the professor behind the Harvard Summer School course “Gender, Food and Culture in American History." An early look: "The best toast I ever tasted," 1939 (photo 1); “How to enjoy your 1951 General Electric refrigerator-food freezer combination,” (photo 2); students participating in a cooking class, ca. 1929-34 (photo 3).</p>
